'''Kashirin Morozov''' (January 29, 1964 - May 17, 1994) was a Russian astronaut for Roscosmos. His promising career was cut short when he was killed during his first research mission at the age of 30. Prior to becoming an astronaut, he previously worked as a firefighter, police officer, computer programmer, and even served in the Russian Air Force as a distinguished fighter pilot. He deserted the military in his third year of service when he was denied a discharge in response to landmine explosion injuries he suffered from his first and only deployment.

==Early life==
Kashirin was born in Kazan, Russia to stay-at-home mother Akinfeeva Yurievich (born 1945) and firefighter Ustinov Morosov (born 1946). He had a stepfather named Boris Putin (born 1946), a receptionist whom Akinfeeva married from 1966 to 1969. He also had a half-brother named Igor Fedorov (born 1970), a cameraman for Maestro TV.

